en_192148_0	The consumers say that a bad smell in emanating from the water being distributed from the Biyagama Water Purification Plant over the last few days.
en_192148_1	Because of this, the consumers in Kelaniya, Wattala, Ragama, and Biyagama are inconvenienced.
en_192148_2	Hiru News contacted General Manager of National Water Supply and Drainage Board's production division, S. Sumanaweera said as a result of the recent floods, the water from paddy fields has entered the Purification Plant.
en_192148_3	He said that no odour is coming out from the water that is being distributed now.
en_192148_4	Meanwhile, demanding a 25% salary hike, NWSDB employees have stopped attending to work during weekends.
